Fragment: write-index-html — Create the necessary files. In `index.html`, set up the basic structure: a title, viewport meta tag, a dark body background (`background-color: #222`), and a `<canvas id="chessCanvas">` element. Create `game.js` and include a basic initialization/constants section in it.
`index.html` must contain:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Chess AI</title>
    <style>
        body { background-color: #222; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; height: 100vh; margin: 0; }
        canvas { border: 5px solid #444; background-color: white; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <canvas id="chessCanvas" width="720" height="720"></canvas>
    <script src="game.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
In `game.js`, define the initial setup logic:
```javascript
// game.js
const WIDTH = 720;
const HEIGHT = 720;
const SIDE_LENGTH = 90;
const COLOR_DARK = "#795548";
const COLOR_LIGHT = "#F0D9B5";

// Initial state definitions (as constants/global variables)
// Initialize the empty boardState[8][8] structure, currentTurn = "White", gameStateStatus = "IN_PROGRESS", etc.
// Call the initialization function to draw the initial board grid.
function initializeGame() {
    const canvas = document.getElementById('chessCanvas');
    if (!canvas) return;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

    // Board Drawing (Using the full loop from Q3 response):
    for (let r = 0; r < 8; r++) {
        for (let c = 0; c < 8; c++) {
            const cellColor = ((c + r) % 2 === 0) ? COLOR_DARK : COLOR_LIGHT;
            const x = c * SIDE_LENGTH;
            const y = r * SIDE_LENGTH;

            ctx.fillStyle = cellColor;
            ctx.fillRect(x, y, SIDE_LENGTH, SIDE_LENGTH);
        }
    }
    // Placeholder: Draw initial pieces here later.
    console.log("Game Canvas Initialized.");
}
window.onload = initializeGame;
```

